extends ../base.pug

include mixins/postCards.pug
include mixins/postList.pug
include mixins/sectionHeading.pug
include mixins/socialLinks.pug

block pageContent
  main
    section
      +header("About me")

      .grid.grid--reverse-md
        .grid__item
          img.image--profile(src="/assets/images/profile/mike-carter-office-talk.webp" alt="Mike Carter talking to a group of people in an office environment" width="475" height="381")

          h2.heading--small Core technologies
          ul.technologies
            li.technologies__item
              strong Ruby:
              span.technologies__tag Rails
              span.technologies__tag Hotwire
              span.technologies__tag Hotwire Native
            li.technologies__item
              strong JavaScript:
              span.technologies__tag Node.js
              span.technologies__tag TypeScript
              span.technologies__tag React
              span.technologies__tag Next.js
            li.technologies__item
              strong Databases:
              span.technologies__tag PostgreSQL
              span.technologies__tag MySQL
              span.technologies__tag Redis
            li.technologies__item
              strong Infrastructure:
              span.technologies__tag AWS
              span.technologies__tag GCP
              span.technologies__tag Docker
              span.technologies__tag Kamal
            li.technologies__item
              strong AI:
              span.technologies__tag Orchestration
              span.technologies__tag Code Generation
              span.technologies__tag RAG

        .grid__item
            p.lead I'm Mike Carter, a principal full-stack software engineer with two decades of experience designing, building, and scaling commercial web applications.

            p As a Software Architect at Holiday Extras, I shaped technical direction across a 100+ team, and was a driving force behind migrating their core booking platform to a React SPA that's still processing thousands of bookings per day. I architected Laced's platform from its earliest days, and helped scale it to handle millions in transactions. At RIFT, I led the technical transformation of their tax refund claims process from manual to self-service, opening access to hundreds of thousands of claimants.

            p I've founded two companies, grown distributed engineering teams, and delivered across the full stack from cloud infrastructure to native mobile. I operate where architecture meets business strategy — technology selection, data model design, migrating millions of sensitive records under strict compliance constraints. I'm most valuable when the problem isn't which framework to use, but how to change a running system under real commercial pressure without breaking the business that depends on it.

            +socialLinks("social-links")


    section#work-history
      +sectionHeading("Work", "work", "Over 13 years I've worked across organisations from 5-person startups to 500-employee enterprises, at every level from individual contributor to architect to founder.")

      .grid
        .grid__item
          .card
            .card__aside
              .card__image-container
                img.card__image(src="/assets/images/bitbrawn-logo.webp", alt="Bitbrawn logo" width="80" height="74" loading="lazy")
            .card__content
              h3 BitBrawn <span class="card__dates">2021 - Now</span>
              p I founded BitBrawn in 2021 to provide senior technical leadership to companies stuck with web applications they've outgrown. As principal engineer and architect on every engagement, I own the technical strategy — from initial system audit through to delivery — working directly with founders, CTOs, and product directors.

              p <a href="https://bitbrawn.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit BitBrawn →</a>

              h4 Recent projects

              ul.text-list
                li <a href="https://riftrefunds.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button button--client-logo" aria-label="RIFT"><span class="button__logo" style="--logo: url(/assets/images/client-logos/rift.svg); --logo-h: 1.95rem; --logo-w: 6.24rem"></span></a> Continued the modernisation I started at Leaf, upgrading the Rails framework, consolidating RIFT's fragmented data stores into a unified API, and extending the self-service experience to cover the full claims lifecycle. Across both engagements, claim submissions increased 192% and unique sign-ins rose 84%. <br><a href="https://bitbrawn.com/work/rift-legacy-platform-modernisation" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read case study →</a>
                li <a href="https://laced.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button button--client-logo" aria-label="Laced"><span class="button__logo" style="--logo: url(/assets/images/client-logos/laced.svg); --logo-h: 2.1rem; --logo-w: 9.69rem"></span></a> Returned five years after building the original platform to architect multi-market support for Laced's European expansion. Introduced market-level abstractions across the full stack — shipping, pricing, listings, admin — without taking a live marketplace offline. Laced now ships globally. <br><a href="https://bitbrawn.com/work/laced-ecommerce-platform" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read case study →</a>
                li <a href="https://purplebricks.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button button--client-logo" aria-label="Purplebricks"><span class="button__logo" style="--logo: url(/assets/images/client-logos/purplebricks.svg); --logo-h: 1.8rem; --logo-w: 18.44rem"></span></a> Three-month engagement to design and ship a property onboarding flow within a large legacy platform at the UK's biggest online estate agent (500+ employees, £300m+ market cap at peak). Worked within their existing architecture, deployment process, and data model under tight constraints. <br><a href="https://bitbrawn.com/work/purplebricks-property-onboarding" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read case study →</a>
                li <a href="https://allocate.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button button--client-logo" aria-label="Allocate"><span class="button__logo" style="--logo: url(/assets/images/client-logos/allocate.svg); --logo-h: 2.85rem; --logo-w: 7.65rem"></span></a> Took over a booking management platform after the lead developer left without warning or documentation. Mapped dozens of undocumented services, stabilised critical systems, and now lead ongoing modernisation. <br><a href="https://bitbrawn.com/work/allocate-legacy-application-rescue" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read case study →</a>
                li <a href="https://dcthomsonshop.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button button--client-logo" aria-label="DC Thomson"><span class="button__logo" style="--logo: url(/assets/images/client-logos/dc-thomson.svg); --logo-h: 3.3rem; --logo-w: 13.91rem"></span></a> Rebuilt their legacy PHP subscriptions platform using Next.js with a configurable backing CMS. Dramatically simplified the process of purchasing a subscription for their tens of thousands of subscribers.

        .grid__item
          .card
            .card__aside
              .card__image-container
                img.card__image.card__image--lighten-dark(src="/assets/images/logos/leaf.svg", alt="Leaf logo" width="80" height="48" loading="lazy")
            .card__content
              h3 Leaf <span class="card__dates">2016 - 2021</span>
              p As co-founder and Engineering Director at Leaf, I owned strategy and delivery end-to-end. I built a distributed team of seven, shipping Node.js, React, and Rails platforms for clients from early-stage marketplaces to established enterprises. Several are still running at scale today.

              p <a href="https://weareleaf.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit Leaf →</a>

              h4 Notable clients

              ul.text-list
                li <a href="https://holidayextras.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button button--client-logo" aria-label="Holiday Extras"><span class="button__logo" style="--logo: url(/assets/images/client-logos/holiday-extras.svg); --logo-h: 2.1rem; --logo-w: 14.54rem"></span></a> Architected a React Native trip planning app, as an incubated product within Holiday Extras. Designed a Node.js and GraphQL backend, handling all types of trips, from fixed dates and destinations to entirely open-ended. Launched summer 2017. <br><a href="https://weareleaf.com/heha" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read case study →</a>
                li <a href="https://riftrefunds.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button button--client-logo" aria-label="RIFT"><span class="button__logo" style="--logo: url(/assets/images/client-logos/rift.svg); --logo-h: 1.95rem; --logo-w: 6.24rem"></span></a> Led development of RIFT's first self-service claims platform, MyRIFT, replacing an entirely manual process. Built the pre-registration eligibility flow, document upload system, and integrated API lookups for addresses, vehicles, and bank details — achieving 99.8% address accuracy across 20,000+ records. This engagement laid the foundation for a multi-year modernisation I continued at BitBrawn. <br><a href="https://weareleaf.com/rift" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read case study →</a>
                li <a href="https://laced.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="button button--client-logo" aria-label="Laced"><span class="button__logo" style="--logo: url(/assets/images/client-logos/laced.svg); --logo-h: 2.1rem; --logo-w: 9.69rem"></span></a> Architected and built Laced's marketplace platform from scratch using Ruby on Rails and React. Features included product listings, bulk seller tools, Stripe and PayPal integration, and a credit-based bidding system. The platform launched in early 2018 and scaled rapidly through the Covid sneaker boom, clearing £100m+ in total sales. I returned to the platform five years later through BitBrawn to architect their European expansion. <br><a href="https://weareleaf.com/laced" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read case study →</a>

        .grid__item
          .card
            .card__aside
              .card__image-container
                img.card__image(src="/assets/images/logos/holidayextras.svg", alt="Holiday Extras logo" width="80" height="80" loading="lazy")
            .card__content
              h3 Holiday Extras <span class="card__dates">2013 - 2016</span>
              p I joined Holiday Extras as a developer and was promoted to Software Architect within the 100+ strong engineering team. I led the migration of their core booking platform to a React SPA — a system processing 10,000+ bookings per day that's still in production today. I also led development of the company's first React Native mobile app and contributed to engineering practices, CI/CD infrastructure, and technical decision-making across the wider organisation.

              p <a href="https://holidayextras.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit Holiday Extras →</a>

        .grid__item
          .grid__placeholder

    section#projects
      +sectionHeading("Projects", "projects", "Products I’ve designed, built, and operated end-to-end — from architecture and infrastructure through to the App Store.")
      .grid
        .grid__item
          .card
            .card__aside
              .card__image-container
                img.card__image(src="/assets/images/logos/istheresomebody.webp", alt="IsThereSomebody logo" width="80" height="80" loading="lazy")
            .card__content
              h3 IsThereSomebody <span class="card__dates">2024 - Now</span>
              p A support network for friends and family of people suffering with addiction. As sole engineer I own the full stack — a Rails 8 monolith, native iOS and Android apps, and cloud infrastructure. 700+ active users across three countries.
              p <a href="https://istheresomebody.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit IsThereSomebody →</a>

        .grid__item
          .card
            .card__aside
              .card__image-container
                img.card__image.card__image--invert(src="/assets/images/logos/parable.svg", alt="Parable logo" width="101" height="71" loading="lazy")
            .card__content
              h3 Parable <span class="card__dates">2022 - 2023</span>
              p An analytics platform tracking readership behaviour for blog authors. Built with Node.js and React, launched in 2022, and deliberately <a href="/posts/my-first-failed-product">shut down in 2023</a> when the market proved too narrow. A formative lesson in validating demand before writing code.

        .grid__item
          .card
            .card__aside
              .card__image-container
                img.card__image(src="/assets/images/logos/howdy.svg", alt="Howdy logo" width="38" height="29" loading="lazy")
            .card__content
              h3 Howdy <span class="card__dates">2017 - 2022</span>
              p A hosted API for web contact forms — validation, spam filtering, and email delivery with zero backend code. Built at Leaf as an internal tool, opened to the public, and organically grew to 100+ paying users before winding down.

        .grid__item.grid__item--stretch
          .grid__placeholder

